					<div class="text-center">
						<h4>In my video production services tailored for the academic community, I bring a methodical approach to each project.</h4>
					</div>
				</div>
            </div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-12 col-sm-10 offset-sm-1">
					<p>From inception, a refined subject research process underpins my <a href="./strategy">pre-production planning</a>. Using a demonstrated understanding of effective video communication, I collaborate closely with subject matter experts during the strategy phase to ensure their message is optimally conveyed through the video medium. This process generates a creative brief, technical brief, and script. Once we have these in hand, we proceed into the production phase.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row whiteBox">
				<div class="col-12 col-md-10 offset-md-1 col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
					<h1>" ... Without a solid plan costs can escalate rapidly, and the final product may fall short of its intended purpose."</h1>
				</div>
            </div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-12 col-sm-10 offset-sm-1">
					<img class="txt-wrap" src="./assets/images/pic01.jpg" alt="" />
					<p>During <a href="./interviewing">production</a>,During production, I handle setup and operation of cameras, sound, and lighting, while also acting as <a href="./interviewing">interviewer</a> on set, where my approachable and empathetic demeanor fosters an environment of comfort, confidence, and clarity for the speaker. While many academic professionals are seasoned public speakers, the presence of cameras can induce a momentary lapse in composure. I strive to cultivate a stress-free atmosphere, allowing speakers to pause and rephrase as needed, ensuring they project their utmost confidence. Multiple takes are often captured to guarantee the speaker's optimal presentation.</p>
					<p>Post-production starts out with a review of everything that was captured during production, followed by the enhancement of the captured footage through <a href="color">color grading</a>. Next comes the <a href="./editing">editing</a> of interview sound bites and b-roll to craft a succinct monologue or dialogue.  Once we’ve achieved “picture lock”, I integrate opening and closing graphics, lower-thirds for speaker identification, and <a href="./motion">animated infographics</a> to facilitate the audience's comprehension of complex topics. Throughout this process, stakeholders are invited to provide feedback at key stages, ensuring the final product remains aligned with its objectives.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
